\f0\fs24 \cf0 README\
\
This folder has the following scripts (with a short description).\
\
1) Average_Mat.m\
\
Calculates the average of the same interaction matrices coming from different fitted sets. \
\
2) cliffsDelta.m\
 \
Calculates the Cliff\'92s Delta measure between observed and simulated final biomass\
\
3) CompSubcomProps.m\
\
Compares abundances of sub communities. Do this for observed and simulated sub-communities. Supplementary figure 8\
\
4) CorrectionT0.py\
\
Infer the missing time point 0 abundance using a linear fitting on the log abundance from time point 12hours (first measured abundance)\
\
5) CorrectionT0Monod.py\
\
Infer the missing time point 0 abundance assuming a Monod growth. First measured abundance at time point t = 12hours\
\
6) fun_CF_Death_Lyso.m\
\
Function to simulate the SMINT-PARINT model. Calculates the outcome of the combined matrices with SMINT-PARINT parameters.\
\
7) fun_MH_Candidate_Rob_Death.m\
\
SAO-algorithm to search parameter space iteratively. Compute the difference of energy between the current parameters state and the new parameters candidate. Keep the new candidate if 
\f1 rand_val < ratio.  \

\f0 Generate a new candidate in the space 
\f1 S_consumer*S_consumed
\f0 \
 \
8) fun_MH_Candidate_Rob.m\
\
SAO-algorithm to search parameter space iteratively. Compute the difference of energy between the current parameters state and the new parameters candidate. Keep the new candidate if 
\f1 rand_val < ratio.  \

\f0 Generate a new candidate in the space 
\f1 S_consumer
\f0 \
\
9) Increased_Mat.m\
\
Function used to increase the size of an existing matrix by the addition of a 0 row and/or column. For instance, when we have a SxS matrix and we want to initialize a S+1xS+1 matrix from this SxS matrix by adding a new row and column (n_row = index new row, n_col = index new column).\
\
10) MH_Algorithm_21SynCom_CF_Death_PARFOR_Lysobacter_Alone.m\
\
Main script to start the SAO-algorithm for parameter searches. It only fits parameters for Lysobacter keeping the interactions between the SynCom20 member fixed (data set 3 generated from the script MH_Algorithm_CF_Death_PARFOR.m, this index can be changed at line 65, or average over the entire fitted sets can be performed using the function Average_Mat.m).\
The script processes in 4 SAO loops to fit Cross-feeding, Self-inhibition, Resource consumption and Predation. At the end of the last loop it starts again at the first loop until stop criteria is reached (Number of iterations p < N).\
\
